The problem is that this recovery logic might be failing silently or the audio track is genuinely dead and can't be recovered. If the camera stream has no live audio track, it falls back to requesting fresh mic access, but that could fail or take too long. The real issue is likely that between Q1 and Q2, the audio track becomes unusable and the recovery attempt doesn't properly restore it before the onended callback tries to start recording again.

